 The main road running through this    
 area is the{A58 Halifax to Leeds}     
 road.This road splits at{Stump Cross} 
 and the{A6036}goes through{Northowram}
 to{Bradford. Stump Cross}is therefore 
 a very busy junction and is controlled
 by traffic lights. There are eight bus
 routes running through{Stump Cross}at 
 regular intervals, and this is the    
 only form of public transport. To the 
 north the{A644}crosses the{A6036}at{  
{Stone Chair}roundabout and goes from{ 
{Brighouse}to{Denholme Gate}where it   
 meets the{Halifax}to{Keighley}road{   
{A629.}There is only one road running  
 up the{Shibden Valley,}from{Stump     
{Cross}to{Queensbury,}but the{Halifax} 
 bus only goes to{Blake Hill End}before
 turning round and then going on to{   
{Northowram.}This bus only runs every 2
 hours, therefore most people use their
 own cars.
